description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Viaduct Care currently has the following exciting opportunity for a Corporate Services &amp; Business Development Manager within Viaduct Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Details for the post as follows:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Band: Band 7&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hours: Full-Time 37.5 hours per week (Mon – Fri)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tenure: 12 Month Fixed-Term Contract&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Base: Kingsgate House, Stockport / Home-Working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Viaduct Care is the GP Federation and is a partnership of all GP practices across Stockport.&lt;/strong&gt; The federation was formed to empower local GPs to provide the best possible care for patients whilst tackling some of the challenges faced by General Practice by helping doctors and other healthcare professionals work together, share resources and expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our vision is to be consistently recognised for enabling the delivery of high quality patient centred healthcare, which is innovative, equitable, efficient, effective and contributing to a healthy population in Stockport.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a Corporate Services &amp; Business Development Manager to join our team.&lt;strong&gt; You will have a pivotal role to play in leading and supporting the operational delivery and development of the organisation&lt;/strong&gt; and will be responsible for leading, monitoring and reviewing programmes of work within the corporate service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a strong focus on performance improvement, innovation and business development and will also &lt;strong&gt;provide managerial support for the senior team&lt;/strong&gt; ensuring that the organisation complies with its corporate statutory duties, and exercises its functions effectively, efficiently, economically, with good governance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you will provide support and advice to deliver and ensure continuous improvement across the organisation and promote the uptake of best practice initiatives to promote excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Including:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Governance arrangements and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance management and Service improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demand and capacity management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality , safety and effectiveness of the service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion, please contact via.viaductcarehr@nhs.net and a member of the team will contact you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for applications will be Tuesday17th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
